Name: GST MSDK Encoding MJPEG
Description: To validate the fixed function hardware accelerated MJPEG video encoding with specific resolution
Test Environment:
1. Download and install the latest Simics
2. startx &
Test Procedures:
1. gst-launch-1.0 -v filesrc location=/media/Raw_Videos/Puppies_320x240_5frames_NV12.yuv ! videoparse width=320 format=nv12 framerate=30 height=240 ! msdkmjpegenc quality=100 ! avimux ! filesink location=/tmp/Puppies_320x240_5frames.avi
2. gst-launch-1.0 filesrc location =/tmp/Puppies_320x240_5frames.avi ! avidemux ! jpegparse ! msdkmjpegdec ! msdkvpp ! glimagesink
Step Expected Result:
1. Video encoding success.
2. Video playback will not be smooth due to simics limitation
3. Video playback has no corruption.
4. System does not hang or freeze.

Name: The Media sub-system shall be able to improve text output quality with H.265/HEVC SCC
Test Environment:
1. Download and install the latest Yocto BSP
2. startx &
Test Procedures:
1. StartX (#5 need to run in xserver-nodm (penguin)
2. Type something in the terminal to make sure there's text in it.
3. Run "gst-launch-1.0 ximagesrc use-damage=0 num-buffers=120 startx=0 starty=0 endx=800 endy=600 ! video/x-raw,framerate=30/1 ! videoconvert ! msdkh265enc ! h265parse ! filesink location= /tmp/output_normal.265"
4. Run "gst-launch-1.0 ximagesrc use-damage=0 num-buffers=120 startx=0 starty=0 endx=800 endy=600 ! video/x-raw,framerate=30/1 ! videoconvert ! msdkh265enc ! video/x-h265,profile="screen-extended-main" ! h265parse ! filesink location= /tmp/output_scc.265"
5. Compare both the output using "gst-launch-1.0 filesrc location= /tmp/output_normal.265 ! h265parse ! msdkh265dec ! glimagesink & gst-launch-1.0 filesrc location= /tmp/output_scc.265 ! h265parse ! msdkh265dec ! glimagesink"
Step Expected Result:
1. One of the output video (with SCC) should have the text sharper than the other.
2. Video playback has no corruption.
3. System does not hang or freeze.
